text.tspan: Child mortality vs share of children immunized against diphtheria,
On the x-axis: Share of children (12-23 months) that are immunized against diphtheria, pertussis, and tetanus (DPT). On the
y-axis: the share of newborns who die before reaching the age of 5.
Data source: UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (via World Bank); World Health Organization (WHO); UNICEF
